sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT u.username) AS num_users
FROM users u
JOIN moderation_logs ml ON u.user_id = ml.moderator_id;

SELECT DISTINCT p.user_id
FROM posts p
JOIN comments c ON p.post_id = c.post_id AND p.user_id = c.user_id;

SELECT DISTINCT u.user_id, u.role
FROM users u
JOIN comment_reports cr ON u.user_id = cr.user_id;

SELECT COUNT(*)
FROM posts
WHERE user_id = (SELECT user_id FROM users WHERE username = 'Jane Doe');

SELECT DISTINCT c.user_id
FROM comments c
INNER JOIN comment_reports cr ON c.comment_id = cr.comment_id;

external_knowledge:
- 'sown the seeds of wisdom and enthusiasm' reflects users who have written thoughtful posts;
- 'posts with over a thousand likes' represents posts with a score greater than 1000;
- 'casting their golden shields in support' refers to the act of voting (specifically upvoting) on their own posts;
- 'nurturing those posts with insightful comments' indicates comments written by the moderators on their posts;
- 'bringing an audience that exceeds the fertile ground of five thousand engagements' points to a metrics value above 5000, signifying significant audience engagement.

- Popularity here is defined by the number of votes a post attracts;
- Recent activity includes both the count of comments and the actual content of the latest comments;
- The term 'academic posts' refers to those belonging to the 'Academics' category;
- 'Not posted by moderators' excludes posts from users with the 'moderator' role.

- "interested in real estate matters" refers to users who have commented on posts in the "Housing" category;
- "housing-related posts" specifically refers to posts categorized under "Housing";
- "sorted in alphabetical order" means the results are ordered by the post titles in ascending order.
